18 2–905.
19 (A) THE SECRETARY SHALL:
20 (1) ESTABLISH A PROCESS TO PERFORM CAPACITY EXPANSION
21 IMPACT ASSESSMENTS;
22 (2) REQUIRE THE USE OF AN IMPACT ASSESSMENT IN THE
23 DETERMINATIONS REQUIRED UNDER §§ 2–903 AND 2–904 OF THIS SUBTITLE; AND
24 (3) IMPLEMENT THE REQUIREMENTS UNDER THIS SECTION,
25 INCLUDING BY ESTABLISHING:
26 (I) ANY NECESSARY POLICIES, PROCEDURES, MANUALS, AND
27 TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS;

8 SENATE BILL 395
1 (II) PROCEDURES TO PERFORM AN IMPACT ASSESSMENT THAT
2 PROVIDES FOR THE DETERMINATIONS REQUIRED UNDER §§ 2–902 AND 2–903 OF
3 THIS SUBTITLE;
4 (III) CRITERIA FOR IDENTIFICATION OF A CAPACITY EXPANSION
5 PROJECT; AND
6 (IV) RELATED DATA REPORTING FROM LOCAL UNITS OF
7 GOVERNMENT ON LOCAL MULTIMODAL TRANSPORTATION SYSTEMS AND LOCAL
8 PROJECT IMPACTS ON GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS AND VEHICLE MILES
